Purchased items Since this update will be moved to a new game, new gamepasses will be created. This means that if you have the nuclear weapons gamepass you will receive access to nuclear weapons in the new game. You will not however get access to any other gamepass unlocked weapons. This will be done automatically, there is no need for you to DM any staff member or member of the development team to have this done. We also plan on adding several new gamepasses, as the game as a whole will be expanded massively. There are also plans to add a purchasable in-game currency. This currency will not give any benefits in-game, and will function to buy cosmetic items like camouflages and skins. There will also be methods to earn this currency. Early Access There will be early access to the game, in phases. The first phase will be a tester program, which will see members of the discord server fill out an application to become members of the Tester Program. Tester's will have benefits after the game's full release, and I am thinking about making the tester program available for purchase as well. Testers who apply will have the same benefits as Testers who buy access, but reporting bugs and testing each new version of the game will be mandatory for those who apply. The next phase of early access will be a paid access version of the game available to everyone at a lower price. There will be rewards for Early Access players, but they will not be of the same scope as the rewards for Testers. These rewards will likely be cosmetic only. The final phase of access will be an Open Test. This Open Test will be of a completed game, but will not be advertised and will not replace Worldstud. Open Players will receive cosmetic awards as well, but these will not be of the same scale as Early Access Players After that, the game will be fully released and replace Nations: Worldstud. People who play after this happens will not receive any rewards. There is no current timeframe for the release of the game. Staff Applications Staff Applications will be opened next week at the latest. You will first become a Trial Mod, then after passing a set of requirements (likely including Supervised and Unsupervised Patrol Hours, and at least one Staff Training) you will become a full Moderator. Discord Moderator Applications may also be released, although this will likely be to existing members of staff only. Staff Announcement Since inactivity has been plaguing the Staff Team for some time, I will be introducing measures to fix this. Staff members, from Monday, will have a set of requirements to be met weekly. You will have allowances be made for inactivity, but failure to meet these requirements will be met with repercussions, including demotion or removal from the Staff Team.
